    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>West Germanic language that is the national language of Germany and Austria, one of the three official languages of Switzerland, and known in various communities in North and South America, South Africa, and Australia. As a written language German is quite uniform, although there are numerous regional differences in pronunciation and dialect.</Note_Text>
